    "body": "Hi @micieslak, as discussed with John, here are the designs for the inclusion of fees into the airdrop flows and details of how the fees dynamically update as the user changes the details of the `What` and `To` sections.\r\n\r\nFigma designs:\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?type=design&node-id=31142-623644&t=5laKBWNSKCVqTw5o-4\r\n\r\nNote there are 2 variants of the fees panel. One where the user is airdropping one asset type and one where they are airdropping >1 asset type. When airdropping >1 asset type we display the fee for each airdrop on the specified chain along with the total fee. When airdropping 1 asset, we only show the total amount without a breakdown.\r\n\r\nThe validation for the following are also included in the flows:\r\n- Asset total exceeds the balance remaining in the contract\r\n- Transaction fees exceed block gas limit\r\n- Not enough funds to pay gas\r\n\r\nHope that all makes sense - any questions just shout! :)",
